	ECHO PLAYER Holding %a to your ear you hear...%c
	IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 6
		SETITEMVAL -1 5 1
		ECHO PLAYER      For the moon never beams, without bringing me dreams%c     Of the beautiful Annabel Lee;%c     And the stars never rise, but I feel the bright eyes%c     Of the beautiful Annabel Lee;%c     And so all the night tide, I lie down by the side%c     Of my darling -- my darling -- my life and my bride,%c     In the sepulchre there by the sea,%c     In the tomb by the sounding sea.
		SETITEMVAL -1 4 1
	ENDIF
	IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 5
		ECHO PLAYER      But our love it was stronger by far than the love%c     Of those who were older than we --%c     Of many far wiser than we --%c     And niether the angels in heaven above,%c     Nor demons down under the sea,%c     Can ever dissever my soul from the soul%c     Of the beautiful Annabel Lee,
		SETITEMVAL -1 5 6
	ENDIF
	IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 4
		ECHO PLAYER      The angels, not half so happy in heaven,%c     Went envying her and me --%c     Yes! -- that was the reason (as all men know,%c     In this kingdom by the sea)%c     That the wind came out of the cloud at night,%c     Chilling and killing my Annabel Lee.
		SETITEMVAL -1 5 5
	ENDIF
	IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 3
		ECHO PLAYER      And this was the reason that, long ago,%c     In this kingdom by the sea,%c     A wind blew out of a cloud, chilling%c     My beautiful Annabel Lee;%c     So that her high-born kinsman came%c     And bore her away from me,%c     To shut her up in a sepulcher%c     In this kingdom by the sea.
		SETITEMVAL -1 5 4
	ENDIF
	IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 2
		ECHO PLAYER      I was a child and she was a child,%c     In this kingdom by the sea;%c     But we loved with a love that was more than love --%c     I and my Annabel Lee;%c     With a love that the winged seraphs of heaven%c     Coveted her and me.
		SETITEMVAL -1 5 3
	ENDIF
	IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 1
		IFVAR ITEMVAL4 = 0
			ECHO PLAYER      It was many and many a year ago,%c     In a kingdom by the sea,%c     That a maiden there lived whom you may know%c     By the name of Annabel Lee;%c     And this maiden she lived with no other thought%c     Than to love and be loved by me.
			SETITEMVAL -1 5 2
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
